_data.title: Installation & Configuration

children.value: You can install the package via composer:
You can publish the config file with:

_data.text:
You can install the package via composer:

``` bash
composer require defstudio/telegraph
```

You can publish the config file with:
```bash
php artisan vendor:publish --tag="telegraph-config"
```

_data.text: ## Creating a new Telegram Bot 1. Go to [@BotFather](https://t.me/botfather) on Telegram. 2. Send `/newbot`, to start creating a new Bot and setting its name and username. 3. take note of the bot **token**. 4. Now you need to allow your Bot to send direct messages, so send `/setjoingroups` to @BotFather, select your Bot and click Enable: 5. (optional) To let your bot to listen for commands (like `/chatid`) you need to enable privacy mode: send `/ 6. Save the bot token into your .env file. ```dotenv TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=XXXXXX:XXXXXXXX-XXXXXXXXXX ```
